JOHANNESBURG - Exactly three years after the accident when Top Billing television presenter Simba Mhere was killed, driver Preshalin Naidoo was found guilty of culpable homicide by the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Wednesday. READ: Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere dies Magistrate David Mahango said, in handing down judgement, that "the court finds that the State has proven the facts beyond reasonable doubt that the accused wrongfully and negligently caused the collision that caused the death of Simba Mhere and Kady-Shay O'Bryan". The deadly crash took place on William Nicol Drive in Fourways in northern Johannesburg. African News Agency